cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks. The use of deep convolutional neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves classification, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of neural networks for feature representation could also suggest that it belongs to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
